   [113]cylus99

Clear the cin buffer in c++?

   I have a simple loop which runs through
   cin>>typed;
   and some more code 20 time.
   My problem is that if i type a space at the cin point, the next time
   through the loop the typed is already filled and it skips over it. I
   understand I need to clear the buffer, but how? thanks
   Follow
   Report Abuse
   Are you sure you want to delete this answer? (BUTTON) Yes (BUTTON) No

